        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued August 11 at 5:23PM CDT by NWS Lubbock TX</headline>
        <description>At 523 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles northeast of Pep, or 9 miles west of Littlefield, moving
northeast at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Amherst.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, seek shelter inside a building.</instruction>
